Job Posting Title:   SE_Project Management Planning & Support_Senior
Description:   Project Planner with focus on Vehicle Build Management at Group Trucks Technology

At the Project and Product Strategy Office we are proud to navigate and lead the Volvo Group’s transition into the future of sustainable transports. As Vehicle Build Manager at Heavy Duty Range you will be part of a high performing team of experts within project and program management. You will lead and influence the program builds over time and secure the assurance activities towards these program builds. By making sure that the builds successfully meet the intended targets you are part of securing a predictable product launch to our customers. To succeed with your tasks, you will use your expertise in project management together with some well proven methods and tools. You will work independently but you will not be alone. In our team of driven and passionate colleagues the culture is friendly and supportive.

Your main focus will be as the Vehicle Build Manger at Heavy Duty Range for program builds and driving the way we work in these areas forward. You will do that by having these core responsibilities:

•       Consolidate the part status towards program builds and address any deviations to the concerned projects
•       Structure and plan for cross-functional follow up of the parts towards builds
•       Manage and follow up the late handling foras
•       Be part and support in the program build securement foras
•       Make lessons learned and drive the way of working forward with efficiency- and quality improvements

Required competences and experiences:
•       University/Master’s degree in engineering or equivalent
•       At least 5 years of work experience including build or component planning
•       Experience of project management or equivalent leadership of component development
•       Knowledge in business intelligence tools, e.g. Excel, Power-Bi, preferred
•       Skilled in facilitating meetings, real and virtual
•       Analytical and well organized is a must
•       You show ownership mentality with a strong drive for results solving complicated task

We offer you an opportunity to work with the best of the best within program- and project management at Volvo, a possibility to gain knowledge within all different functions such as engineering, sales, production and purchasing. You do so in an open environment that appreciates your improvement proposals. Interested? Looking forward for your application.

Senior: position typically requires >5 years relevant experience

Volvo Group is an equal opportunity employer that values diversity in our workplace and we welcome all applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, gender or cultural background.

Job Posting Start Date:   2024-04-01
Job Posting End Date:   2024-10-31
Location:   Göteborg
Job Family:   Project Management  Support
Price: 774 sek/h

